    "The source of this event is a magnitude 6.1 earthquake occurring at a depth of 123.2 km to the southeast of the Loyalty Islands, New Caledonia (Supplement).",
    "It is possible that event source mechanisms of a similar appearance are due to crevasse formation or propagation in the subsurface or to quakes in the firn layer, which generate seismic waveforms similar to those of tectonic earthquakes at teleseismic distances (Lough et al., 2015).",
    "Based on the peak amplitude, this event is classified as Teleseism I (> 3.5, log a.u.).",
    "The event in Fig. 5c that begins on 11 January 2011 at 09:27:07 UTC corresponds to a tectonic teleseismic event, with a peak amplitude that corresponds to the range allotted to Teleseism II (≤ 3.5, log a.u.).",
